      "side": 1,
      "message": "Line 303: `onAudioCongestion()` hard-codes severe-loss reduction factors `0.45f` and `0.55f`, bypassing the validated `audioReductionFactor` configuration. This makes tuning ineffective and can even make severe-loss behavior less aggressive than a configured lower reduction factor. Derive severity scaling from the configured factor and clamp once.\n```suggestion\n    float reductionFactor \u003d cfg_.audioReductionFactor;\n    if (audioLoss \u003e 10.0f)\n        reductionFactor \u003d std::min(reductionFactor, 0.45f);\n    else if (audioLoss \u003e 5.0f)\n        reductionFactor \u003d std::min(reductionFactor, 0.55f);\n```",
      "revId": "92894d2d834ddf8e552f96e368fee2d2a8380d7d",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
    },
