      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 151: The controller starts in `State::Probing`, and `setTargetBitrate()` does not move it to Stable. As soon as normal RR feedback arrives on a new call, `evaluateState()` takes the `State::Probing` path and increases bitrate even though no prior congestion/decrease occurred. This can ramp every RTCP interval until max bitrate purely because the call is healthy. Initialize to Stable consistently with `reset()` and the state comment.\n```suggestion\n    State state_ {State::Stable};\n```",
      "revId": "92894d2d834ddf8e552f96e368fee2d2a8380d7d",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
    },
    {
