      "writtenOn": "2026-05-31T16:45:44Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 729: `setupVideoBitrateInfo()` calls `bwController_.setLimits()` on every RTCP/audio QoS pass, but `setLimits()` only clamps the current target. If codec settings change and the current bitrate is now outside the new bounds, the encoder is not updated unless a later congestion event changes the target. This leaves the active encoder bitrate outside negotiated limits. After updating limits, sync/apply the clamped controller target when it differs from `videoBitrateCurrent`.\n```suggestion\n        bwController_.setLimits(codecVideo-\u003eminBitrate, codecVideo-\u003emaxBitrate);\n        if (bwControllerInitialized_) {\n            videoBitrateInfo_.videoBitrateCurrent \u003d std::clamp(videoBitrateInfo_.videoBitrateCurrent,\n                                                               codecVideo-\u003eminBitrate,\n                                                               codecVideo-\u003emaxBitrate);\n            bwController_.syncAppliedBitrate(videoBitrateInfo_.videoBitrateCurrent);\n        }\n```",
      "revId": "92894d2d834ddf8e552f96e368fee2d2a8380d7d",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
    },
