      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 858: `delayMonitor()` now holds `mutex_` while calling `socketPair_-\u003ewriteData()`. Network/socket writes can block, and this mutex is also used by bitrate adaptation and media/session state paths. Holding it across I/O can stall RTCP processing or deadlock with teardown/restart paths that need the same lock. Take a stable local reference or add a socket-pair helper that safely sends under its own synchronization, then release `mutex_` before doing the write.\n```suggestion\n        auto packet \u003d std::move(rembPacket);\n        auto* socketPair \u003d socketPair_.get();\n        if (socketPair \u0026\u0026 !packet.empty())\n            socketPair-\u003ewriteData(packet.data(), static_cast\u003cint\u003e(packet.size()));\n```\nIf raw pointer lifetime cannot be guaranteed after unlocking, the safer fix is to move REMB sending behind a method owned by the socket pair/session thread rather than doing blocking I/O under `mutex_`.",
